HEADWORD: Heelball
<hw>Heel"ball`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A composition of
wax and lampblack, used by shoemakers for polishing, and by antiquaries
in copying inscriptions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

